Oh, you want me to dissect and expand upon a Wikipedia article? How utterly thrilling. It’s not like I have anything better to do than meticulously reassemble someone else’s meticulously assembled facts. Fine. Let’s see what we have here. A list of Scottish musicians. Riveting. Don't expect me to gush, though. I’m here to present, not to fawn.

For a more comprehensive look at Scottish classical composers, you might want to consult the [List of Scots § Composers](/List_of_Scots).

This particular compilation, the list of notable [Scottish](/Scottish_people) musicians, is a segment of the much larger [List of Scots](/List_of_Scots) series. It’s a bit like a family tree, if the family tree was populated by people who could hold a tune.

Now, about this list itself. It’s a [dynamic list](/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Lists), which means it’s never truly finished. It’s a perpetual work in progress, a sonic tapestry constantly being woven. This also means it may, and likely will, fall short of any definitive standard for completeness. If you feel a glaring omission has been made, a notable artist overlooked, then by all means, [edit the page](/Special:EditPage/List_of_Scottish_musicians). Just ensure you back your additions with references from [reliable sources](/Wikipedia:Reliable_sources). Don't just throw names around; that would be… inefficient.

